question: What must be done to perform any Utility program in the MIF Commissioning?
answer: To perform any Utility program in the MIF Commissioning, it is necessary to activate the related button and then use the machine's Start button to start the operation. This must be done in MDA mode.

Database backup can be performed in different modes
 Backup at regular intervals
 Backups are called according to the number of the current backup
 The current backup number is used as an identifier in addition to the main file name. For example the FPSuiteMainDB database backups will be named FPSuiteMainDB1
FPSuiteMainDB2 and so on. The last backup file is always saved with the number 1
 The number of backup copies to keep is indicated during the backup configuration
phase
 The database is not compressed into a .zip file
 Daily backups
 Backups are called according to the day of the week. For example the FPSuiteMainDB
database backups will be named FPSuiteMainDB.Monday FPSuiteMainDB.Tuesday
and so on. The database is compressed into a .zip file

question: What does checking the "Wait for finish" checkbox (Number 3) imply in the task scheduling system?
answer: Checking the "Wait for finish" checkbox (Number 3) implies that the task scheduling system will wait for the current task to complete before executing the next task. This means that the system will not proceed with the next task until the previous one has finished, ensuring that tasks are executed sequentially and not concurrently.

6.3.3 Database backup
Database backup can be performed in different modes
 Backup at regular intervals
 Backups are called according to the number of the current backup
 The current backup number is used as an identifier in addition to the main file name. For example the FPSuiteMainDB database backups will be named FPSuiteMainDB1
FPSuiteMainDB2 and so on. The last backup file is always saved with the number 1
 The number of backup copies to keep is indicated during the backup configuration
phase
 The database is not compressed into a .zip file
 Daily backups
 Backups are called according to the day of the week. For example the FPSuiteMainDB
database backups will be named FPSuiteMainDB.Monday FPSuiteMainDB.Tuesday
and so on. The database is compressed into a .zip file

6.3.3 Database backup
Database backup can be performed in different modes
 Backup at regular intervals
 Backups are called according to the number of the current backup
 The current backup number is used as an identifier in addition to the main file name. For example the FPSuiteMainDB database backups will be named FPSuiteMainDB1
FPSuiteMainDB2 and so on. The last backup file is always saved with the number 1
 The number of backup copies to keep is indicated during the backup configuration
phase
 The database is not compressed into a .zip file
 Daily backups
 Backups are called according to the day of the week. For example the FPSuiteMainDB
database backups will be named FPSuiteMainDB.Monday FPSuiteMainDB.Tuesday
and so on. The database is compressed into a .zip file

4. A dropdown menu will appear, allowing you to choose between available languages (e.g., English and Italiano).
5. Select the desired language from the dropdown menu.

6.3.3 Database backup
Database backup can be performed in different modes
 Backup at regular intervals
 Backups are called according to the number of the current backup
 The current backup number is used as an identifier in addition to the main file name. For example the FPSuiteMainDB database backups will be named FPSuiteMainDB1
FPSuiteMainDB2 and so on. The last backup file is always saved with the number 1
 The number of backup copies to keep is indicated during the backup configuration
phase
 The database is not compressed into a .zip file
 Daily backups
 Backups are called according to the day of the week. For example the FPSuiteMainDB
database backups will be named FPSuiteMainDB.Monday FPSuiteMainDB.Tuesday
and so on. The database is compressed into a .zip file
